post_text:
GREAT NEWS from the Dixon R-1 Food Director:

There is no doubt that COVID-19 has impacted all families in some manner, especially so from a financial standpoint. Many of the nation's education organizations have lobbied both the USDE and USDA to extend the waivers and continue offering meals to student at no cost. Last week, the USDA, which has oversight of the school breakfast and lunch programs, announced an indefinite extension of the waivers. Extension of the waivers means, that ALL Dixon R-1 students, for the indefinite future, will receive FREE Breakfast and Lunch.

We ask that if your child has a negative balance that you use this time to try and catch that balance up. If your student has a positive balance, it will remain in their account until we return to normal and everyone goes back to their regular lunch program. Keep in mind this extension could stop at any time and everyone will go back to what they were on to begin with.

#desbulldogpride

Dixon Area Caring-Center
July 21 at 11:04 AM ·

Registration for the Back to School Fair is open!
Come by the Caring Center to get your child registered anytime Monday thru Friday 10 am - 4 pm.
Due to COVID 19, things will be a little different this year. We will be pre-filling your childs new back pack with all of the requested supplies and delivering them to your child's classroom. So there WON'T be a fair for you to attend this year but your child will still get all supplies requested by their teacher. We will miss seeing all of you and your children but want to ensure everyone's safety. Only people who pre-register their child will get backpacks on the first day so make sure to get up here to get registered. If you have any questions please call the Caring Center at 759-3023.

post_text:
Good morning,

This week is Teacher Appreciation Week and I want to reach out to you, our parents, and tell you thank you for all you have done these past few weeks to help educate your child at home. You are your child's first teacher and I realize that these last few weeks have been stressful for everyone involved. Words can never tell you how much I appreciate you, for all you do, and for all you continue to do each and every day. A quote by Henry Ford sums up how I feel, "Coming together is the beginning. Keeping together is progress. Working together is success". Together we are strong! #desbulldogpride

Have a great week, Mrs. Allen.

shared_text:
Missouri Department of Elementary and Secondary Education
May 1 at 5:00 AM ·

Today, we celebrate "School Lunch Hero Day!" Between preparing healthy food, adhering to strict nutrition standards, navigating student food allergies, and offering service with a smile, Missouri nutrition professionals have a lot on their plate on a “normal” day. Extended building closures during COVID-19 required our food service professionals to quickly be innovative and creative to develop ways to continue feeding the Missouri students who rely on school breakfast and lunch each day.

Join us in recognizing these important team members today!

post_text:
Lately, it seems we are on a roller coaster ride that keeps going up; hopefully the end is near and we can get back to "normal". I want to thank you for all that you have been doing at home to educate your child; but I don't want you to stress over schoolwork. In August we will get back on track. Right now, I need you to share your calm, your strength, and your laughter with your child. Make a new memory daily. We are in this together and I appreciate all you do. Keep safe, stay healthy, and give your child a hug or a high five from me!

Mrs. Allen
Principal
Dixon Elementary School

post_text: Parents: It’s finally that time......The ONLINE BOOK FAIR is up and running. Please use the link in the picture to access our DES Online Book Fair. Dixon R-I School District
April 10 at 5:30 PM ·

Starting Friday night on April 10th, DHS will be joining schools around the country by turning on our baseball and softball field lights on Friday nights at 8:20 p.m., which is 20:20 military time and leaving them lit for 20 minutes and 20 seconds to honor the class of 2020.

On Friday nights in April, look toward DHS to see the glow of our support for our graduating class of 2020.

We would like to encourage anyone that has a sign in town to go ahead and congratulate our seniors. Let’s celebrate the class of 2020 and show them some love!

post_text:
Due to ongoing COVID-19 concerns, Dixon R-I will remain closed for on-site classes through 04/03. We will re-evaluate the week of 03/30 and tentatively resume 04/06.

Teachers are posting and distributing lessons one week at a time. We plan to initiate our distance education plan this coming Monday, March 23. We are asking students to begin their first week’s lessons at that time.

Teachers will hold virtual office hours to assist students from 9am-1pm each school day.

Assignments sent home to students will be graded. Finished assignments should be turned in digitally.

Additional academic support will be provided by a Homework Hotline that will be offered through Dawg Pound.

Thank you for your continued patience and support. #desbulldogpride

Healthy Futures Pulaski County
September 13, 2019 at 5:36 PM ·

We have great news!!! In an effort to inspire the kids of Pulaski County up and running, the HFPC will be GIVING AWAY 100 entries into the Leapfrog 5k taking place on October 4 at 6:00 p.m. at the Waynesville City Park to kids between the ages of 6-11. This race is held in conjunction with the Frog Hill Half/10k taking place the next day and is a part of the Healthy Futures Pulaski County Race Series. It's first come, first served, so get your child signed up froghillhalf.com today using the code: ACTIVEKIDS2019 at registration!!!!
#hfpcmo #pchcmo #activekids #runfroghill #leapfrog5k
